node.text:
I think I found my favorite sound. 

Do things your own way. 

Part time OR full time entrepreneurship is 🔐 🔑 to financial freedom.

You don’t need to have millions to make millions. 

You don’t need to make millions in your network marketing business in order to make millions as an entrepreneur. 

This is my story. Kinda 😉 

Drop a heart if you love it! 
#bosslee

node.text:
The first personality type book I ever read sorted the personalities into birds.

I took the test. It told me I was an eagle. As if I didn’t know that.

regardless of what the book said I remember learning about bald eagles in elementary school. I remember learning about how rare they are, how dominant they are, how they operate on their own and how they can be commanding.

they represent the entire United States of America. I knew I resonated with that.

The other birds were owl, peacock, and dove. 

Which one do you think you are?

Characteristics: Domineering, strong-willed, independent, vocal, competitive and shrewd. How to motivate an eagle: Recognise their successes, offer them variation and give them the status they crave. Be firm and direct in your handling.

Read: also #bosslee

node.text:
I am in pursuit of things that set my soul on fire. 

I am posting this on a Saturday which means I know most of you are going to be put in situations where you feel pressured into doing things that you don’t really feel like.

here is your permission to say no.

If you needed this reminder to set your life on the right track, because after all there are only so many hours in a day & You cannot say yes to everything, drop HELL YES below.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by JESSIE LEE | BOSSLEE MLM PRO on August 13, 2021 tagging @josephhaefstattooer. May be an image of 1 person and high-heeled shoes.

node.text:
Why network marketing? The confidence. 

I’ve developed into one hell of a woman over the last 10 years of direct sales and network marketing.

Countless events with personal development Titans, nearly a book a week for a decade, lord knows how many hours of podcasts, zoom calls and who knows what else…

The amount of this 👏 is 👏 me 👏 . And I love me, and also I really like me. 

My God. I pray you all become better versions of yourself daily so you know who should absolutely have access to your beautiful, developed energy ❤️

What is your favorite way to develop? 

#bosslee

node.text:
It’s so easy to talk about the butterfly but I encourage you to not forget about that ugly, painful, struggling caterpillar phase. 

Your simple actions will yield great rewards. But, I can pretty much promise you it’s going to suck.

A caterpillar never becomes a beautiful butterfly without the struggle of metamorphosis. If you help a caterpillar get out of its cocoon the butterfly will never fly. I don’t know many people that look at caterpillars and see how beautiful they are. But everybody embraces the butterfly.

why can’t we embrace this in life?

nobody’s coming to save you. But I mean that in such a beautiful way. Be your own hero. 

And fly, baby, fly. 

Tag your accountability partner that might be in their caterpillar phase below. 🦋 

and drop me some butterfly emoji‘s if you love this reminder. 🦋🦋🦋🦋

#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing? 

Because I love to give.

I always wanted to be a person that could give back the way that some people helped give back to me and my family when I grew up in a family that just really didn’t have much to show. I’ve been told more times than I can count that I get our team too many incentives and I just don’t care.

I’ve never charged for a retreat yet, I’ve never charged them for Swag, and it’s kind of a running joke that every time we run something that does cost money Jessie Lee does not understand what the budget is LOL

I’ve given hundreds of thousands of dollars to charities, I don’t ever talk about it but I’ve spent God knows how much money on adoptions, I’m able to give back in ways that I just genuinely never thought would be possible.

if you watch my stories you might’ve seen the story the other day where I was stopped in an elevator by a man who said “are you #BOSSLEE?” Of course I said yes. And he said he’s been following me on social media for years when in downtown Dallas he watched me stop my Lamborghini to reach out and hand a homeless man a bunch of cash.

I don’t think I ever tell you guys about that. It’s just what I do. I reach into my wallet I grab whatever bills are there and I hand them to people. I’d rather not assume why they’re homeless or what they’ve done wrong in their lives.

so why do I give? Because I serve an abundant God. I completely understand that everything that I give comes back tenfold. And, selfishly…DAMN it feels good. 

If that resonates in some way with you drop a heart below ❤️ 
#bosslee
